The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Feb. 1: The contentious issue of hiking the ceiling of foreign direct investment (FDI) in the telecom sector may be considered among other issues at a meeting of the Union cabinet here tomorrow. Finance minister P. Chidambaram had, in his budget speech last year, announced the government?s decision to increase the FDI limit in telecom to 74 per cent from 49 per cent.

 New Delhi, Feb. 1: Air-India and Indian Airlines, which are preparing to launch their initial public offers by next fiscal, may offload 10 to 15 per cent of the equity and set aside some shares for employees, official sources said today. The government could either enhance the equity base of these airlines or dilute it without changing their public-sector character, they added.

 Mumbai, Feb. 1: The Reserve Bank today put in place revised procedures for compounding of contravention, except hawala dealings, under the Foreign Exchange Management Act (Fema) to reduce transaction costs.

 New Delhi, Feb. 1: The Centre?s gross tax collection grew by over 18 per cent to Rs 1,94,231 crore in the first nine months of this fiscal from Rs 1,64,170 crore last year, mainly due to a robust growth in direct tax mop-up.

 New Delhi, Feb. 1: The Union power ministry is believed to have cleared Power Finance Corporation?s (PFC) proposed initial public offer to enhance its equity by 10 per cent. It would soon be placed before the cabinet.




